[start section id="20103"]

I had the pleasure to meet Mr. Kelly, a 68-year-old male from Mc Alpin District of Columbia.  He came accompanied by his wife.  I spent one and one-half hours with the patient and also reviewed extensive Postville Good Samaritan Medical Center records.
1.  1979 - seminoma, presented with a 25-cm anterior mediastinal mass, primary tumor.  This was resected followed by postoperative radiation therapy followed by a single dose of Cytoxan.
2.  Developed cardiomyopathy caused by radiation therapy, underwent two heart transplantations, July 2003.
3.  September 20, 2010, laparoscopic right hemicolectomy for T3, N2b adenocarcinoma of the colon,13 of 17 resected lymph nodes involved with metastasis, poorly-differentiated adenocarcinoma, signet ring cell.
Mr. Kelly has recovered from surgery without any complication and is up and about and asymptomatic.  I enjoyed very much spending at least one and one-half hours with the patient and his wife, talking to him, examining him, and reviewing extensive Postville Good Samaritan Medical Center records.
I refer the reader to the excellent note of my colleague Diane Hall, NP who saw the patient in initial consultation in the hospital after colon cancer surgery, September 22, 2010.

